08/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- French Foreign Minister Michel Barnier described Albania as a source of moderation and stability in the Balkans, after his meeting with Prime Minister Fatos Nano on Tuesday (7 September). Barnier said Tirana has contributed positively to regional policy. He pledged France's continuing support for Albania's integration into European structures. 
Also Tuesday, Albanian President Alfred Moisiu met with new UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen. Moisiu said defining Kosovoâ€™s status is of vital importance to regional stability. Jessen-Petersen said the goal is a multiethnic Kosovo where minorities' interests are protected. (Albanian Daily News - 08/09/04; ATA - 07/09/04) 
